      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS ARI (10) is a progressive Victorian mare who is racing in fine form, beating the boys to win her last two outings at Melton. Up in the gradings but she returns to her own sex and while she cops a wide draw she has won at this venue before. SNAP SHOT NZ (11) was solid when beaten only 2.4m from a similar draw in a Winter Gift heat last week. She looks suited back against the mares and managed a win at this circuit and distance last month. SWEET DREAMS NZ (4) faces her biggest test yet but is unbeaten in three starts since crossing from NZ and does get the barrier advantage over a few of her main rivals. ULTIMATE DIVA (8) didn't have the best of luck when beaten 6m last time. Recorded three straight placings prior, racing wide but sticking on for third here two back. Include.",
